4109 - GH - Locations Claims : This report shows the following claim information by location for the current year and is run monthly:   Penske Accident Report # (AL/GL claims); GBS Claim Number (WC claims); date of accident or injury, unit number, employee name, state where the accident occurred, accident description, claim type, claim status and Total $s incurred.   Used to look at claim detail at the location level for the current year.

4110 - GH - Claims By Comparison : This report is an Area report.   It provides a comparison between the current year and the prior year and is run monthly (for example:  Claims as of 9/30/11 vs Claims as of 9/30/10).   The report is split into 2 sections.  The first section  - AL/GL, Collision and Cargo.   The number of accidents, claim $s associated and the Cost Per $1,000 / Revenue is provided by type.   The second sections is Workers Compensation.   This section provides the # of injuries and $s associated by Medical Only, Lost Time and then Combined.   **Note - the collision and cargo info. is pulled from the Penske Accident Reporting System (AS400).   The # of claims and $s associated are not populated in the AS400.  This report is used to view and compare claims for locations within an Area for the current year and previous year at the same points in time.
